cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper proposes a method for boosting generative models, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on deep generative models for complex data such as images, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of hidden variable meta-models such as RBM and VAE suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the extension of the boosting framework to semi-supervised learning, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the combination of the boosting framework with the multiplicative boosting framework suggests a connection to statistical learning (cs.SD).
